cc:Work.dc:title: ebook reader
cc:Work.dc:description: This drawing is intended to represent an ebook reader device generally, without being specific to any particular make or model (though, unavoidably, some aspects of the design may be somewhat reminiscent of various models). \n \nTo avoid any trademark entanglements, the titles listed on the reader in this image are all public domain works, taken from Project Gutenberg's "Top 100" list. In case anyone wants to edit the image to list different books on the reader, the font I used is called Anja Eliane Accent (which you can find via a web search).
